The paper proposes a framework for deep generative learning, which involves learning generative models via variational gradient flow on probability spaces. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it has practical applications in these sub-fields. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.IT, in that order.
